North Korea’s foreign minister said during a speech at the United Nations on Saturday that the lack of lifting sanctions only deepens North Korea’s lack of trust in the United States and there is no way that the country unilaterally renounces nuclear weapons in such circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the annual General Assembly that North Korea had taken "significant measures of goodwill" last year, such as halting nuclear and missile tests, dismantling the nuclear test site and committing to non-proliferation of weapons and nuclear technology.
