Ri did not mention plans for the second summit between Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump, which the U.S. leader spoke about earlier this week at a U.N. forum.
Instead, the minister drew attention to three meetings between Kim Jong Un and South Korean leader Moon Jae-in over the past five months, after which he added: “If South Korea were a party to denuclearization and not the United States, then there would be no such impasse.”
However, the tone of Ri’s speech was completely different compared to last year when he said during the UN General Assembly that North Korea’s missile targeting on U.S. territory is inevitable after “Mr. Evil President” Trump misfired (Mr. Evil President Trump himself).
This year at the UN forum Trump, who last year threatened to “totally destroy” North Korea, praised Kim Jong Un for his courage in taking steps to disarm, but also said there was still a lot of work to be done, and also said that until North Korea is able to defend itself against North Korea.
